"Read It Later" instead of "Starred" and "Favorites" - \par
\par
It could be much more convincing to put it this way - especially for average (non-technical) users. It is highly probable that marking articles as starred often serves this purpose: to easily go back to them in some later - spare time. So 'Read It Later' could give a better idea of how this feature may benefit the user. - \par
\par
\par
"Important Articles" instead of "Mark(ed) as starred" - \par
\par
A dedicated filter placing chosen articles into 'Favorites' (or 'Read It Later') most probably will be used to preserve the content which user finds most important and bring it to a foreground via notification. - \par
\par
